mixture probabilistic PCAConsider a model\[x_i = \mu_k + W_k z_i + \varepsilon_k, ~~ if~y_{ik}=1,y_{ij}=0,i\neq j.\tag{1.1}\]where \(x_i \in R^p, z_i \in R^q, \varepsilon_k\sim N(0, \sigma^2_kI_p)\),\(z_i \sim N(0, I_q), W_k \in R^{p\times q}, y_i \sim Multinormial(1,\pi),\pi \in R^K\).First, it performs clustering, then conducts PCA. The following contents are divided into three parts:
evaluate full-data loglikelihood \(l(\theta)\);
take posterior expectation of latent variables on \(l(\theta)\), and obtain Q-function;
